---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="Aerospace engineering student at Florida Tech. North Attleboro to Melbourne.">
  <main class="about-main">

    <header class="about-header">
      <p class="label" style="color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 1rem;">About</p>
      <h1>The mountain only asks:<br /><em>will you keep climbing?</em></h1>
    </header>

    <!-- BODY -->
    <section class="about-body">
      <p class="mood-label label">Body</p>

      <p>
        I grew up in North Attleboro, Massachusetts — got there in fourth grade after moving
        around enough to understand that adaptation isn't optional, it's just life. I played
        baseball and football until I realized football was taking too many of the brain cells
        I was planning to use for other things. So I gave it up. One brain. Better make it count.
      </p>

      <p>
        I work at Starbucks. I smile at Larry as I ring up his Decaf Pike with 2 Splenda and nonfat
        milk refill at 8am and tell him I'm doing great, despite running on 3 hours of sleep after
        studying for a differential equations exam. That emotional masking is real work — a different
        kind of difficult than rocket science, and in some ways harder. Service exposes you. You can't
        hide behind being smart.
      </p>

      <p>
        I recently started running. My first attempt was in Doc Martens. Within half a mile my
        lungs were negotiating terms and conditions. There is a certain humility that comes from
        physical reality refusing to participate in your self-image. I'm training for the Philadelphia
        Half Marathon in November, raising money for the Emily Whitehead Foundation — a cause that
        means something personal, not something I picked off a list.
      </p>

      <p>
        I have two callings: mountains and cities. Cities for the density, the feeling that something
        is always being built or torn down. Mountains to remember none of it matters as much as I think
        it does. The mountain doesn't care where you went to school, how many views your writing has,
        or how organized your Notion is. It only asks one thing.
      </p>
    </section>

    <blockquote class="pull-quote">
      "systems do not answer the ache, but they give the ache somewhere to go"
    </blockquote>

    <!-- SYSTEM -->
    <section class="about-body">
      <p class="mood-label label">System</p>

      <p>
        I chose Florida Tech because I wanted to get away and start my own version of things.
        Not running from anything — just ready to find out what I was made of when nobody who
        knew me was watching. Aerospace engineering felt like the right kind of hard.
      </p>

      <p>
        I think about engineering the way some people think about philosophy. Not just rockets
        and software — engineering is a way of confronting assumptions, a discipline of learning
        from failure fast enough to stay in the game. I used to be afraid of failure. Now I
        think it's probably the fastest teacher available, and I actively try to be the least
        experienced person in the room as often as possible. That's not humility. That's how
        you close the gap.
      </p>

      <p>
        Right now I'm in the Aerospace Systems Lab doing sensor pipeline work on traffic validation
        data. I'm also building a nuclear project finance model from scratch — not because someone
        assigned it, but because I wanted to understand why SMRs keep failing under private financing
        when the underlying physics works. The answer turns out to be mostly about discount rates and
        policy structure, not the reactor. That finding matters.
      </p>

      <p>
        I build systems for my own life too — career dashboards, resume generators, file sorters.
        I reach for structure when things get chaotic. But the writing keeps teaching me that
        systems are containers, not answers. They give the ache somewhere to go. They don't resolve it.
      </p>
    </section>

    <blockquote class="pull-quote">
      "the artist is built in errands"
    </blockquote>

    <!-- SOUL -->
    <section class="about-body">
      <p class="mood-label label">Soul</p>

      <p>
        Outside of all of it, I write. Poetry, essays, brain dumps at 1am about what it means
        to be a student and a person simultaneously. I write about money anxiety and creative
        devotion and the loneliness that is the price of a certain kind of freedom. I write
        because the technical world needs somewhere to be honest about itself, and I need
        somewhere to be honest about me.
      </p>

      <p>
        My writing is lowercase on purpose. Not an aesthetic choice — a philosophical one.
        The sentence that starts without a capital letter is already less interested in impressing
        you. That's the register I'm trying to work in.
      </p>

      <p>
        What I'm trying to figure out right now is how to take it easy. How to sit with a
        thunderstorm or the smell of something good without immediately turning it into a problem
        to solve. I'm wired for systems and what comes next — and I'm learning, slowly, that
        the small things are not a distraction from the work. They might be the point.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="about-photos">
      <figure class="about-photo young">
        <img src="/photos/young-parker.jpg" alt="Parker, younger" />
        <figcaption>North Attleboro era.</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="about-photo current">
        <img src="/photos/river-portrait.jpg" alt="Parker by the river" />
        <figcaption>Melbourne, FL.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

    <section class="principles">
      <h2>How I operate</h2>
      <ul class="principles-list">
        <li><em>Build before you feel ready.</em></li>
        <li><em>Document the mess.</em></li>
        <li><em>Be the least experienced person in the room as often as possible.</em></li>
        <li><em>Failure is the fastest teacher.</em></li>
        <li><em>Discipline is not aesthetics — it is returning.</em></li>
        <li><em>The field notes matter.</em></li>
        <li><em>The small things are not a distraction. They might be the point.</em></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about-quick">
      <div class="quick-grid">
        <div class="quick-item">
          <span class="label">Education</span>
          <p>B.S. Aerospace Engineering<br />Florida Institute of Technology<br />Expected May 2028 · GPA 3.3</p>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-item">
          <span class="label">Research</span>
          <p>Aerospace Systems and Propulsion Lab<br />ROS · Gazebo · Foxglove · MCAP<br />SmartSignals Edge-AI Traffic Systems</p>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-item">
          <span class="label">Writing</span>
          <p>Ground Control on Substack<br />Poetry, essays, field notes<br />The human condition, mostly</p>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-item">
          <span class="label">Located</span>
          <p>Melbourne, FL<br />From North Attleboro, MA<br />Born in Providence, RI</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .about-main {
    max-width: 780px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 8rem 2rem 6rem;
  }

  .about-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .about-header h1 em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .mood-label {
    display: block;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  }

  .about-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .about-body:first-of-type {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .about-body p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.9;
    color: var(--dim);
  }

  .about-body p strong { color: var(--text); }
  .about-body p em    { color: var(--text); font-style: italic; }

  /* Pull quotes between sections */
  .pull-quote {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 2.5vw, 1.75rem);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 2.5rem;
    padding: 0;
    border: none;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  /* Photos */
  .about-photos {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0 4rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .about-photo {
    margin: 0;
    background: #fff;
    padding: 8px 8px 28px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .about-photo.young {
    width: 180px;
    transform: rotate(-2deg);
  }

  .about-photo.current {
    width: 220px;
    transform: rotate(1.5deg);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .about-photo img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: 220px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .about-photo.young img { height: 240px; }

  figcaption {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    color: #888;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  /* Principles */
  .principles {
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
    padding: 2.5rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .principles h2 { margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }

  .principles-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.9rem;
  }

  .principles-list li {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--dim);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .principles-list li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-style: normal;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  /* Quick facts */
  .about-quick { margin-top: 1rem; }

  .quick-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .quick-item p {
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--dim);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
</style>
